      <title>Massive six story deep sinkhole opens up in New Zealand</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANA massive sinkhole has opened up on a dairy farm in New Zealand, exposing 60,000-year-old volcanic rock deposits.   The sinkhole appeared after several days of heavy rainfall on a farm near the North Island town of Rotorua, according to CBS News. Experts say rains dissolved underground limestone over thousands of years, which eventually caused the ground to collapse and form the canyon. The sinkhole is 20 meters deep, roughly six stories, and around 220 meters long, about the length of two soccer fields.  Volcanologist Brad Scott told TVNZ that the fissure appeared on the crater of a long-dormant volcano. Scott said the deposits at the bottom of the sinkhole were the original 60,000-year-old volcanic deposits that came out of the crater.  RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of sinkhole2. The sinkhole3. The sinkhole is 6 stories deep and the length of 2 soccer fields4. The sinkholeVOICEOVER (in English): "A massive sinkhole has opened up on a dairy farm in New Zealand, exposing 60,000-year-old volcanic rock deposits. According to CBS News, the sinkhole appeared after several days of heavy rainfall on a farm near the North Island town of Rotorua.""Experts say rains dissolved underground limestone over thousands of years, which eventually caused the ground to collapse and form the canyon." "The sinkhole is 20 meters deep, roughly six stories, and around 220 meters long, about the length of two soccer fields."  "Volcanologist Brad Scott told TVNZ that the fissure appeared on the crater of a long-dormant volcano. Scott said the deposits at the bottom of the sinkhole were the original 60,000-year-old volcanic deposits that came out of the crater."SOURCES: CBS News, Sky News, ScienceAlerthttps://www.cbsnews.com/news/new-zealand-sinkhole-on-dairy-farm-near-north-island-town-of-rotorua/https://news.sky.com/story/giant-sinkhole-opens-into-60000-year-old-volcano-in-new-zealand-11362925https://www.sciencealert.com/biggest-ever-sinkhole-in-new-zealand-rips-gaping-chasm-two-football-fields-long-rotorua-north-island***]]></description>
