      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANThe Paris knifeman, who killed one person and wounded four others in an attack on Saturday evening, had previously been flagged as a potential security risk by authorities. Police have identified the attacker as 20-year-old Khamzat Azimov. Azimov shouted "Allahu akbar" in the busy Opera district around 9 p.m. Saturday night as he began his attack. According to the BBC, eyewitnesses said Azimov was dressed in a black tracksuit and had a beard. Azimov attempted to enter several restaurants and bars, but was blocked by people inside. Authorities arrived on the scene in minutes. Police first attempted to stop Azimov with a stun-gun, but when that failed, they shot him dead.  The man killed was a 29-year-old from Luxembourg, while the four wounded included two men in their 30s, one 26-year-old woman and one 54-year-old woman. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of the knife attack2. Knifeman beginning his knife attack3. Knifeman attempting to enter a restaurant4. Knifeman lying on street after being shot by policeVOICEOVER (in English): "The Paris knifeman, who killed one person and wounded four others in an attack on Saturday evening, had previously been flagged as a potential security risk by French authorities." "Police have identified the attacker as 20-year-old Khamzat Azimov. Azimov shouted 'Allahu akbar' in the busy Opera district around 9 p.m. Saturday night as he began his attack." "Azimov attempted to enter several restaurants and bars, but was blocked by people inside." "Authorities arrived on the scene in minutes. Police first attempted to stop Azimov with a stun-gun, but when that failed, they shot him dead."  SOURCES: REUTERS, BBC, NEW YORK POSThttps://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-security-attacker/paris-knife-attacker-was-french-citizen-born-in-chechnya-idUSKCN1IE07Ahttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44096595https://nypost.com/2018/05/13/knifeman-in-paris-terror-attack-was-flagged-as-potential-threat/***]]></description>
